<paragraph blockId="77.[113,1089,989,1621]" box="[144,536,1053,1077]" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Metathoracic wings fully developed.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="77.[113,1089,989,1621]" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">
Mesoventrite strongly microreticulate, impunctate, almost glabrous, with a distinct excavation between median carina and transverse carina (
<figureCitation box="[651,748,1117,1141]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="76.[152,183,1535,1554]" captionTargetBox="[154,1115,655,1524]" captionTargetId="figure-172@76.[151,1126,650,1524]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="Fig. 44. Leiodes hijikatai sp. nov.A – body, dorsal view; B – ditto, lateral view; C – antenna; D – elytral punctures; E – mesoventrite, lateral view. Scale I: 1 mm for A and B; II: 0.5 mm for C; III: 0.5 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272557/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Fig. 44E</figureCitation>
); median carina of mesoventrite low (
<figureCitation box="[168,266,1149,1173]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="76.[152,183,1535,1554]" captionTargetBox="[154,1115,655,1524]" captionTargetId="figure-172@76.[151,1126,650,1524]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="Fig. 44. Leiodes hijikatai sp. nov.A – body, dorsal view; B – ditto, lateral view; C – antenna; D – elytral punctures; E – mesoventrite, lateral view. Scale I: 1 mm for A and B; II: 0.5 mm for C; III: 0.5 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272557/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Fig. 44E</figureCitation>
); metaventrite sparsely pubescent, strongly microreticulate except for almost smooth middle portion.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="77.[113,1089,989,1621]" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">
Protibiae gradually and very feebly widening from base towards apex (
<figureCitation box="[908,1008,1213,1237]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="77.[113,144,856,875]" captionTargetBox="[124,1072,220,836]" captionTargetId="figure-249@77.[113,1088,208,839]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="Fig. 45. Leiodes hijikatai sp. nov. A – male fore leg, ventral view; B – male hind leg of paratype, ventral view; C – ditto of holotype; D – male protibia, dorsal view; E – male metafemur, dorsal view; F –male abdominal sternite 8. Scale I: 0.5 mm for A; II: 0.5 mm for B and C; III: 0.2 mm for D; IV: 0.2 mm for E; V: 0.5 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272559/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Fig. 45D</figureCitation>
); tarsomeres 2–4 of protarsi and mesotarsi expanded (
<figureCitation box="[617,716,1245,1269]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="77.[113,144,856,875]" captionTargetBox="[124,1072,220,836]" captionTargetId="figure-249@77.[113,1088,208,839]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="Fig. 45. Leiodes hijikatai sp. nov. A – male fore leg, ventral view; B – male hind leg of paratype, ventral view; C – ditto of holotype; D – male protibia, dorsal view; E – male metafemur, dorsal view; F –male abdominal sternite 8. Scale I: 0.5 mm for A; II: 0.5 mm for B and C; III: 0.2 mm for D; IV: 0.2 mm for E; V: 0.5 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272559/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Fig. 45A</figureCitation>
); metafemur with a distinct ventral rectangular projection (
<figureCitation box="[365,531,1277,1301]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="77.[113,144,856,875]" captionTargetBox="[124,1072,220,836]" captionTargetId="figure-249@77.[113,1088,208,839]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="Fig. 45. Leiodes hijikatai sp. nov. A – male fore leg, ventral view; B – male hind leg of paratype, ventral view; C – ditto of holotype; D – male protibia, dorsal view; E – male metafemur, dorsal view; F –male abdominal sternite 8. Scale I: 0.5 mm for A; II: 0.5 mm for B and C; III: 0.2 mm for D; IV: 0.2 mm for E; V: 0.5 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272559/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Figs. 45B, 45C</figureCitation>
) and a small dorsal projection posteroapically (
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="77.[113,144,856,875]" captionTargetBox="[124,1072,220,836]" captionTargetId="figure-249@77.[113,1088,208,839]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="Fig. 45. Leiodes hijikatai sp. nov. A – male fore leg, ventral view; B – male hind leg of paratype, ventral view; C – ditto of holotype; D – male protibia, dorsal view; E – male metafemur, dorsal view; F –male abdominal sternite 8. Scale I: 0.5 mm for A; II: 0.5 mm for B and C; III: 0.2 mm for D; IV: 0.2 mm for E; V: 0.5 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272559/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Fig. 45E</figureCitation>
); metatibiae bearing less than ten small robust spines at about basal 1/3 of internal margins, weakly curved in 
<typeStatus box="[304,397,1341,1365]" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[412,507,1341,1365]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="77.[113,144,856,875]" captionTargetBox="[124,1072,220,836]" captionTargetId="figure-249@77.[113,1088,208,839]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="Fig. 45. Leiodes hijikatai sp. nov. A – male fore leg, ventral view; B – male hind leg of paratype, ventral view; C – ditto of holotype; D – male protibia, dorsal view; E – male metafemur, dorsal view; F –male abdominal sternite 8. Scale I: 0.5 mm for A; II: 0.5 mm for B and C; III: 0.2 mm for D; IV: 0.2 mm for E; V: 0.5 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272559/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Fig. 45C</figureCitation>
) and strongly curved in 
<typeStatus box="[767,859,1342,1366]" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">paratype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[874,971,1341,1365]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="77.[113,144,856,875]" captionTargetBox="[124,1072,220,836]" captionTargetId="figure-249@77.[113,1088,208,839]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="Fig. 45. Leiodes hijikatai sp. nov. A – male fore leg, ventral view; B – male hind leg of paratype, ventral view; C – ditto of holotype; D – male protibia, dorsal view; E – male metafemur, dorsal view; F –male abdominal sternite 8. Scale I: 0.5 mm for A; II: 0.5 mm for B and C; III: 0.2 mm for D; IV: 0.2 mm for E; V: 0.5 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272559/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Fig. 45B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="77.[113,1089,989,1621]" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">
Abdominal sternite 8 moderately curved (
<figureCitation box="[593,690,1373,1397]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="77.[113,144,856,875]" captionTargetBox="[124,1072,220,836]" captionTargetId="figure-249@77.[113,1088,208,839]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="Fig. 45. Leiodes hijikatai sp. nov. A – male fore leg, ventral view; B – male hind leg of paratype, ventral view; C – ditto of holotype; D – male protibia, dorsal view; E – male metafemur, dorsal view; F –male abdominal sternite 8. Scale I: 0.5 mm for A; II: 0.5 mm for B and C; III: 0.2 mm for D; IV: 0.2 mm for E; V: 0.5 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272559/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Fig. 45F</figureCitation>
); aedeagus slender (
<figureCitation box="[907,1076,1373,1397]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="78.[151,182,936,955]" captionTargetBox="[207,1070,224,913]" captionTargetId="figure-240@78.[196,1081,216,933]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="Fig. 46. Leiodes hijikatai sp. nov.A – aedeagus, dorsal view; B – ditto, lateral view; C – inner sac, dorsal view. Scale I: 0.5 mm for A and B; II: 0.1 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272561" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272561/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Figs. 46A, 46B</figureCitation>
); median lobe weakly expanded laterally in apical half of lateral margins and feebly curved at apex in dorsal (
<figureCitation box="[277,376,1437,1461]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="78.[151,182,936,955]" captionTargetBox="[207,1070,224,913]" captionTargetId="figure-240@78.[196,1081,216,933]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="Fig. 46. Leiodes hijikatai sp. nov.A – aedeagus, dorsal view; B – ditto, lateral view; C – inner sac, dorsal view. Scale I: 0.5 mm for A and B; II: 0.1 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272561" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272561/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Fig. 46A</figureCitation>
), moderately curved in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[765,863,1437,1461]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="78.[151,182,936,955]" captionTargetBox="[207,1070,224,913]" captionTargetId="figure-240@78.[196,1081,216,933]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="Fig. 46. Leiodes hijikatai sp. nov.A – aedeagus, dorsal view; B – ditto, lateral view; C – inner sac, dorsal view. Scale I: 0.5 mm for A and B; II: 0.1 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272561" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272561/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Fig. 46B</figureCitation>
); each paramere bearing two apical setae and one transparent slender lobe (
<figureCitation box="[701,801,1469,1493]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="78.[151,182,936,955]" captionTargetBox="[207,1070,224,913]" captionTargetId="figure-240@78.[196,1081,216,933]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="Fig. 46. Leiodes hijikatai sp. nov.A – aedeagus, dorsal view; B – ditto, lateral view; C – inner sac, dorsal view. Scale I: 0.5 mm for A and B; II: 0.1 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272561" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272561/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Fig. 46A</figureCitation>
); inner sac without distinct sclerites (
<figureCitation box="[215,314,1501,1525]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="78.[151,182,936,955]" captionTargetBox="[207,1070,224,913]" captionTargetId="figure-240@78.[196,1081,216,933]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="Fig. 46. Leiodes hijikatai sp. nov.A – aedeagus, dorsal view; B – ditto, lateral view; C – inner sac, dorsal view. Scale I: 0.5 mm for A and B; II: 0.1 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272561" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272561/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Fig. 46C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="77.[113,1089,989,1621]" box="[144,353,1532,1557]" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[144,234,1532,1557]" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[144,227,1532,1557]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Female</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="78" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="77" pageNumber="70" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="77.[113,1089,989,1621]" lastBlockId="78.[151,1127,1036,1348]" lastPageId="78" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,356,1565,1589]" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Hoshina, 2012" authorityName="Hoshina" authorityYear="2012" box="[369,547,1567,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Leiodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="77" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hijikatai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[369,547,1567,1590]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">Leiodes hijikatai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[552,635,1566,1589]" pageId="77" pageNumber="70" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hoshina, 2012" authorityName="Hoshina" authorityYear="2012" box="[770,850,1567,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Leiodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="77" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="araii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[770,850,1567,1590]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="70">L. araii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[856,938,1566,1589]" pageId="77" pageNumber="70" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the form of the elytral punctures but can be distinguished from it by having dark reddish brown antennal club and having the metafemur with a distinct ventral posteroapical projection (
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="77.[113,144,856,875]" captionTargetBox="[124,1072,220,836]" captionTargetId="figure-249@77.[113,1088,208,839]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="Fig. 45. Leiodes hijikatai sp. nov. A – male fore leg, ventral view; B – male hind leg of paratype, ventral view; C – ditto of holotype; D – male protibia, dorsal view; E – male metafemur, dorsal view; F –male abdominal sternite 8. Scale I: 0.5 mm for A; II: 0.5 mm for B and C; III: 0.2 mm for D; IV: 0.2 mm for E; V: 0.5 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272559/files/figure.png" pageId="78" pageNumber="75">Figs. 45B, 45C</figureCitation>
). In contrast, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hoshina, 2012" authorityName="Hoshina" authorityYear="2012" box="[408,490,1069,1092]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Leiodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="78" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="araii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[408,490,1069,1092]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="75">L. araii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[498,582,1068,1091]" pageId="78" pageNumber="75" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has the antennae almost uniformly brown and the metafemora weakly expanded posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[605,772,1100,1124]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="70.[150,181,1518,1537]" captionTargetBox="[208,1034,787,1494]" captionTargetId="figure-192@70.[200,1077,780,1503]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="Fig. 40. Leiodes araii sp. nov.A – male fore leg, ventral view; B – female fore leg, ventral view; C – male hind leg, ventral view; D – female hind leg, ventral view; E – male protibia, dorsal view; F – female protibia, dorsal view; G – male metafemur, dorsal view; H – female metafemur, dorsal view. Scale I: 0.5 mm for A and B; II: 1 mm for C and D; III: 0.2 mm for E and F; IV: 0.2 mm for G and H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272549" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272549/files/figure.png" pageId="78" pageNumber="75">Figs. 40C, 40D</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Hoshina, 2012" authorityName="Hoshina" authorityYear="2012" box="[789,967,1101,1124]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Leiodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="78" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hijikatai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[789,967,1101,1124]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="75">Leiodes hijikatai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[972,1054,1100,1123]" pageId="78" pageNumber="75" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is also similar to the European 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gyllenhal, 1810)" baseAuthorityName="Gyllenhal" baseAuthorityYear="1810" box="[401,735,1132,1156]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Leiodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="78" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctulata">
<emphasis box="[401,542,1133,1156]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="75">L. punctulata</emphasis>
(Gyllenhal, 1810)
</taxonomicName>
by the irregularly punctate elytra and the mesoventrite bearing an excavation, but can be separated from it by having the lateral margins of the median lobe feebly curved at the apex in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[889,989,1196,1220]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="78.[151,182,936,955]" captionTargetBox="[207,1070,224,913]" captionTargetId="figure-240@78.[196,1081,216,933]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="Fig. 46. Leiodes hijikatai sp. nov.A – aedeagus, dorsal view; B – ditto, lateral view; C – inner sac, dorsal view. Scale I: 0.5 mm for A and B; II: 0.1 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272561" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272561/files/figure.png" pageId="78" pageNumber="75">Fig. 46A</figureCitation>
). In contrast, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gyllenhal" baseAuthorityYear="1810" box="[151,293,1229,1252]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Leiodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="78" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctulata">
<emphasis box="[151,293,1229,1252]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="75">L. punctulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the median lobe protuberant apically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272561" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4272561" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4272561/files/figure.png" pageId="78" pageNumber="75" startId="78.[151,182,936,955]" targetBox="[207,1070,224,913]" targetPageId="78">
