<subSubSection pageId="78" pageNumber="75" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="78.[151,1127,1036,1348]" pageId="78" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1260,1284]" pageId="78" pageNumber="75">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is dedicated to a very popular samurai Toshizô Hijikata (1835–1869) who was born in the Tama Region in which the 
<typeStatus box="[661,707,1292,1316]" pageId="78" pageNumber="75">type</typeStatus>
locality of this species is situated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[151,823,1324,1348]" pageId="78" pageNumber="75" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="78.[151,1127,1036,1348]" box="[151,823,1324,1348]" pageId="78" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,298,1324,1348]" pageId="78" pageNumber="75">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[304,369,1324,1347]" name="Japan" pageId="78" pageNumber="75">Japan</collectingCountry>
: Honshu (
<collectingRegion box="[475,545,1324,1348]" country="Japan" name="Tokyo" pageId="78" pageNumber="75">Tokyo</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[597,680,1324,1348]" country="Japan" name="Nagano" pageId="78" pageNumber="75">Nagano</collectingRegion>
Prefectures).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
